Package com.hp.jipp.encoding

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    Attribute<T>
    An IPP attribute, which is a named list of 0 or more values. Values are parsed into the most natural Java type that can encode the supplied data.
    AttributeCollection
    An ordered collection of attributes as defined in RFC3382.
    AttributeType<T>
    A named attribute type which may be used to construct interface Attribute objects containing values of type T.
    Stringable
    An object that has a native string representation.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    AttributeGroup
    A tagged group of attributes.
    BaseAttribute<T>
    Overridable implementation for any subclass of interface Attribute.
    BooleanType
    An attribute type containing boolean values.
    CollectionType<T extends AttributeCollection>
    An attribute type for collections of T.
    DateTimeType
    An attribute type based on Calendar type.
    EmptyAttribute
    An attribute consisting only of an out-of-band tag and no values.
    Enum
    A machine-readable integer code paired with a human-readable name.
    EnumType<T extends Enum>
    An attribute type based on class Enum type of T
    IntOrIntRange
    An int or range of int
    IntOrIntRangeType
    Attribute type for attributes whose values are either integers or IntRange objects
    IntRangeType
    An attribute type containing IntRange values.
    IntType
    An attribute type containing integer values.
    IppInputStream  
    IppOutputStream  
    IppPacket
    An IPP packet consisting of header information and zero or more attribute groups.
    KeyValueType
    Represents an attribute type encoded in key-value pairs.
    KeyValues
    A map of keys to values where keys and values are both strings.
    KeywordType
    An attribute type containing keyword values as Strings.
    MediaSizes  
    Name
    Describes a name object, which may or may not have a language string.
    NameType
    An attribute type for name types, which can be encoded with either Tag.nameWithoutLanguage or Tag.nameWithLanguage.
    OctetsType
    A type for octetString types, represented natively as ByteArray values.
    OtherOctets
    An attribute value formatted as an array of octets.
    OtherString
    An attribute value formatted as a String.
    Resolution
    Describes a printing resolution.
    ResolutionType
    An attribute type containing class Resolution values.
    ResolutionUnit
    A unit of measurement used to describe resolution.
    StringType
    A type of attribute which is most clearly represented as a string
    Tag
    Value and delimiter tags as specified by RFC2910 and RFC3382
    TaggedValue
    Any attribute value which does not directly correspond to a common Java type.
    Text
    Describes a text object, which may or may not have a language string.
    TextType
    An attribute type for text types, which can be encoded with either Tag.textWithoutLanguage or Tag.textWithLanguage.
    UnknownAttribute
    An otherwise unrecognized attribute, including at least one value, containing values of any legal type that can be expressed in IPP form.
    UntypedCollection
    An attribute collection (see RFC3382) represented as a list of interface Attribute objects.
    UntypedEnum
    An enum lacking any formal Enum type (meaning its values cannot be decoded).
    UriType
    An attribute type for uri attributes.
